#FEUIASSessionistas
#ConSESStrateOnGroove

message.text:
Sabi nila, kapag tumigil daw ang mundo mo...ibig sabihin YOU'RE A GREAT SINGER! 🤩

Congratulations mga ka-IAS! Always remember that showcasing your talents is a pathway filled with numerous opportunities. Remember to try and go on because that alone, takes a lot of courage. 🥰

Sessionistas called and we heard you on our different stages. Now we’ll say CONGRATULATIONS!🥳 CHECK YOUR E-MAILS! 🫶

#NewVoiSESSUnlocked
#FEUIASSessionistas
#ConSESStrateOnGroove 

Caption by Maclyn Seraspe & Kaye Amoguis
Pubmat by Precious Nikole Tungpalan

Enthusiasts of books, art, and stationary gathered at SMX Convention Center on September 13, Saturday  to attend this year’s Manila International Book Fair.

The five day event lasting from September 10 to 14 featured book showcases from local and international authors, book signing events, and exclusive discounts on stationary and literature.

message.text:
Take me back to MIBF 📖

Enthusiasts of books, art, and stationary gathered at SMX Convention Center on September 13, Saturday  to attend this year’s Manila International Book Fair.

The five day event lasting from September 10 to 14 featured book showcases from local and international authors, book signing events, and exclusive discounts on stationary and literature. 

Authors from publishing companies as well as indie authors had the chance to showcase their amazing works ranging from picture books, comics, novels and more, and interact with their adoring fans.

AJ Vile, a local reverse harem author cited in an interview with Kuhaku Media that reading books and any literature is essential to the current Generation Z to have a more moderated sense of thought.

Documentation from: Kaedehara Kazumi and Berenice Meghan Sy Lim
With Reports from:  Kaedehara Kazumi

#Kuhakumedia
#MIBF2025 
#GetLit

message.text:
Take me back to MIBF 📖

Enthusiasts of books, art, and stationary gathered at SMX Convention Center on September 13, Saturday  to attend this year’s Manila International Book Fair.

The five day event lasting from September 10 to 14 featured book showcases from local and international authors, book signing events, and exclusive discounts on stationary and literature. 

Authors from publishing companies as well as indie authors had the chance to showcase their amazing works ranging from picture books, comics, novels and more, and interact with their adoring fans.

AJ Vile, a local reverse harem author cited in an interview with Kuhaku Media that reading books and any literature is essential to the current Generation Z to have a more moderated sense of thought.

Documentation from: Kaedehara Kazumi and Berenice Meghan Sy Lim
With Reports from:  Kaedehara Kazumi

#Kuhakumedia
#MIBF2025 
#GetLit
